  "texts": [
    "Recurrent neural networks (RNN) convert text into a sequence of words.",
    "It is designed to get the dependency between the word and the structure of the text.",
    "The most popular architecture of RNN is long short-term memory (LSTM) in tree structure, word relation and document topic.",
    "RNNs capture the pattern in the time dimension, while convolutional neural networks (CNN) capture the pattern in the space dimension.",
    "CNN works well in long-range semantic comprehension and detects the local and position-defined pattern."
